post_text:
The August 17th School Board Meeting will take place at the Polson High School Auditorium at 5:30pm as well as virtually on our website using the link below which also includes a form to submit a public comment to be read aloud at the meeting. During Phase 2 COVID restrictions the district is limiting gatherings to 50 or fewer people in one space and will be forced to limit in-person attendance by the public to approximately 25 people. Members of the public will be admitted on a first come first serve basis until capacity is reached. Masks are required for entry.

Live Streaming Link: https://www.polson.k12.mt.us/board-of-trustees/live-streaming-board-meeting

post_text:
The Polson School District summer meal program has been temporarily suspended effective immediately. A district food service worker tested positive for COVID-19. The district has notified the Lake County Health Department and will follow their guidance in responding to this incident and will restart the meal program on August 11th.

The food worker has been isolated, and contact tracing is ongoing. All food preparation staff wear masks and gloves, and we do not believe that anyone who received and/or consumed food products prepared by this worker is at an increased risk of exposure to COVID-19. There is no evidence that food or food packaging is associated with the transmission of COVID-19 regardless of the status of the worker.

https://www.polson.k12.mt.us/news/1685397/summer-meal-program-temporarily-suspended
shared_text:
POLSON.K12.MT.US
Summer Meal Program Temporarily Suspended
text:
The Polson School District summer meal program has been temporarily suspended effective immediately. A district food service worker tested positive for COVID-19. The district has notified the Lake County Health Department and will follow their guidance in responding to this incident and will restart the meal program on August 11th.

The food worker has been isolated, and contact tracing is ongoing. All food preparation staff wear masks and gloves, and we do not believe that anyone who received and/or consumed food products prepared by this worker is at an increased risk of exposure to COVID-19. There is no evidence that food or food packaging is associated with the transmission of COVID-19 regardless of the status of the worker.

The District has provided information regarding families who qualify for Free and Reduced meals to the Department of Health and Human Services (DPHHS). The DPHHS should be sending those families a letter in the mail informing them of the Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) program, as well as a loaded EBT card to assist them with meal costs. Should you have any questions or comments, please call the District Office at (406) 883-6355.

Students and families, please take a few minutes to read through our updated Distance Learning page that will help you get connected with your teachers via Google Classroom. Included are videos produced by students that walk you through getting your computer set up and signed in. The teachers have been working hard at learning this platform and are excited to have a new set of tools to connect with you starting next week! Paper packets will be provided on an as-needed basis. Each school has been contacting families who reported they don't have a computer at home to arrange for a loaner device (contact your school office or teacher next week if you think we missed you).

Governor Bullock directed Montana’s public K-12 schools to close starting tomorrow, March 16 until March 27. District leadership is gathering information and planning next steps. Details are limited at the moment, please follow this page for further information and updates.
